Whisper Audio Transcription App (Streamlit + DeepInfra)

A Streamlit-based web application for speech-to-text transcription using the Whisper Large V3 (Distil) model via DeepInfra.
The app supports both audio file uploads and live microphone recording, enabling quick and interactive transcription workflows.

This project demonstrates secure API usage, multimodal AI integration,and real-world deployment considerations for speech-to-text systems.

Features

Transcribe uploaded audio files (.wav, .mp3, .ogg)

Record live audio via microphone and transcribe instantly

Fallback support using sounddevice or PyAudio

Fast inference using DeepInfra-hosted Whisper model

Secure API key handling using environment variables

Simple and intuitive Streamlit UI


Architecture Overview

User (Browser)
   ↓
Streamlit UI
   ↓
Audio Input (Upload / Live Mic)
   ↓
Audio Preprocessing (WAV)
   ↓
DeepInfra Whisper API
   ↓
Transcription Output


## Tech Stack
- Python
- Streamlit
- Whisper (Distil Large V3)
- DeepInfra API
- NumPy, SciPy, SoundDevice, PyAudio
